Program: Great Lives
Title: Ernest Hemingway
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m000fwym
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 6 Mar 2020
Michael Palin first came across his Great Life when he was studying for school exams, his love of Ernest Hemingway has never gone away. He, along with expert Naomi Wood tell Matthew Parris why this twentieth century legend is a Great Life. Producer :Perminder Khatkar. First broadcast on BBC Radio 4 in 2014. Show less